author: Jami Frankenberry
title: Are you ready for some Monday Night Football?
text:
The heavy rains that whipped through Hampton Roads on Friday washed out all of the area's high school football games. Only Maury, which travelled to Lynchburg to play Liberty Christian, played Friday.
Otherwise, 10 games have been moved to Monday (weather permitting), including the key Beach District match-up between No. 5 Cox and No. 7 Bayside. The game between Nansemond River and Indian River has been rescheduled for Oct. 13 at a time to be determined.
Also, next week's region golf tournaments have been moved.
Monday's football schedule:
• Portsmouth Christian at Greenbrier Christian, 6 p.m.
• Landstown at Kellam, 6 p.m.
• Kempsville vs. Ocean Lakes, 6:30 p.m. at VB Sportsplex
• Booker T. Washington vs. Churchland, 7?p.m. at Powhatan Field
• Cox at Bayside 7 p.m.
• King's Fork at Great Bridge, 7?p.m.
• Lakeland at Deep Creek, 7 p.m.
• Norcom at Wilson, 7 p.m.
• Tallwood at First Colonial, 6 p.m.
• Norfolk Academy at Hampton Roads Academy, 5 p.m.
The new region golf tournament schedule:
• The one-day 4A East Region tournament is now scheduled for Wednesday at Oceana in Virginia Beach.
• The two-day 5A South Region tournament is scheduled for Tuesday and Wednesday at The Hamptons.
• The one-day 6A South Region tournament is scheduled for Wednesday at Magnolia Green Golf Club in Moseley.
